cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with unsupervised learning of data distributions using deep learning, specifically Variational Auto-Encoders (VAEs), and applies it to medical image analysis for anomaly detection and localization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as well as Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of VAEs also suggests that the paper may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the experiments conducted on medical images suggest that the paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
